.SH NAME
.PP
check-for-reboot.bash
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
check-for-reboot.bash
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This command will check if Ubuntu is expecting to be rebooted.
It will display details if a reboot is needed and exit with a status of
1 otherwise it will not return any output and exit with a status of 0.
.PP
This script will check for \[lq]safe_to_reboot.py\[rq] and
\[lq]safe_to_reboot.bash\[rq] in the PATH as well as in /Sites and will
run that script to check if a reboot requires extract steps beyond the
usual \[lq]sudo reboot\[rq] command.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Here\[cq]s the typical use case
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sudo apt update;sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt autoremove; sudo apt autoclean
check-for-reboot.bash
\f[R]
.fi
